This happens often. Many of the ideas in this thread that inspire stories are derivative, each one sometimes coming up in short prompts, any of the sundry discussions occurring here, or vis a vis exchanges that help develop ideas into cogent story ideas. If you've been inspired by any of the elements and concepts here, you're not alone - if a concept's been topicized here, it's already massively visible. Like Sharks said, you're probably very finely attuned to the content of your writing, and that can subliminally enhance your sensitivity to related tropes when they come up. The topic isn't focusing on you, but the subtext incorporates common tropes with something that's uniquely yours, and hasn't been seen by anyone else, so you're acutely aware and suspicious of it. Try not to dig into it too deeply.
